Here is my solution. 

In our situation, we won't query with partial annotation , we always query with a complete annotation. so prefix index and proper TokenAnalyzer is enough. Here are steps you can follow. 

1. compile following code and package it into a jar then put it in cassandra library path and restart cassandra.

```


package org.apache.cassandra.index.sasi.analyzer;

import java.nio.ByteBuffer;
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.Iterator;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Locale;
import java.util.Map;

import com.google.common.base.Strings;

import org.apache.cassandra.db.marshal.AbstractType;

public class ZipkinStandardAnalyzer extends AbstractAnalyzer
{
    private static final Locale DEFAULT_LOCALE = Locale.getDefault();
    private static final String ZIPKIN_DELIMITER = "░";
    private AbstractType validator;
    private List<String> tokens = new ArrayList<>();
    private Iterator<String> iter;
    
    public ZipkinStandardAnalyzer()
    {
    }

    public ByteBuffer next()
    {
        return this.validator.fromString(iter.next());
    }

    public void init(Map<String, String> options, AbstractType validator)
    {
        this.validator = validator;
    }

    public boolean hasNext()
    {
        return iter.hasNext();
    }

    public void reset(ByteBuffer input)
    {
        this.next = null;
        this.tokens.clear();
        String ann = validator.getString(input);
        ann = ann.toLowerCase(DEFAULT_LOCALE);
        String[] parts = ann.split(ZIPKIN_DELIMITER);
        for (String part : parts)
        {
            if (!Strings.isNullOrEmpty(part))
            {
                tokens.add(part);
            }
        }
        this.iter = tokens.iterator();
    }


    public boolean isTokenizing()
    {
        return true;
    }
}


```


2. replace old annotation index with following statement


```
CREATE CUSTOM INDEX span_annotation_query_idx ON zipkin2.span (annotation_query) USING 'org.apache.cassandra.index.sasi.SASIIndex' WITH OPTIONS = {'analyzer_class': 'org.apache.cassandra.index.sasi.analyzer.ZipkinStandardAnalyzer', 'case_sensitive': 'false', 'mode': 'prefix', 'analyzed': 'true'};

```

3. modify class zipkin2.storage.cassandra.SelectTraceIdsFromSpan as following and deploy your zipkin with new code again.

```

Call<Set<Entry<String, Long>>> newCall(
      @Nullable String serviceName,
      String annotationKey,
      TimestampRange timestampRange,
      int limit
    ) {
      Input input = new AutoValue_SelectTraceIdsFromSpan_Input(
        serviceName,
        // Notice here,we just need to remove all ░
         annotationKey,
        timestampRange.startUUID,
        timestampRange.endUUID,
        limit
      );
      return new SelectTraceIdsFromSpan(
        this,
        serviceName != null ? withServiceAndAnnotationQuery : withAnnotationQuery,
        input
      ).flatMap(new AccumulateTraceIdTsLong());
    }


```



That's all. Hope I've made myself clear.

